вЂ‹DOCUMENTATION OFFICIAL: FLEXDOT v1.0
Author: (Mr.S & Gemini AI)
Platform: Pydroid 3 / Python 3.x
Status: Stable (75% completed)
вЂ‹Language Fundamentals
FlexDot is a Python-based interpreted language designed to be lightweight, logical, and easy to read. Source files must use the .fd extension.
вЂ‹Golden Rules:
Indentation: Blocks inside a check, next, fail, or loop MUST have a 2-space indent so the engine knows they belong to that function.
Comments: Any line starting with # will be ignored by the engine.
вЂ‹Variable Management & Math
FlexDot uses the : operator to assign values and perform calculations.
Syntax: variable_name : value_or_operation
вЂ‹Examples:
Assign Text -> name : Mr.S
Assign Number -> age : 14
Math Operations -> points : points + 10
Booleans -> active : true
вЂ‹Note v0.8a: The engine automatically detects if an operation is mathematical or simple text.
вЂ‹Input/Output Commands (I/O)
show(content): Displays text or variables in the console.
Auto-Detection: If you write a variable name inside the parentheses, FlexDot will display its value.
Example: show(Hello name you have points points)
вЂ‹input(variable_name): Stops the program and waits for user input. The result is saved in the specified variable.
Example: input(answer)
вЂ‹clear: Clears the terminal for a clean UI. (Does not use parentheses).
вЂ‹wait(seconds): Pauses execution. Can use numbers or variables.
Example: wait(1.5) or wait(speed)
вЂ‹Control Logic (Conditionals)
Allows the program to make decisions.
вЂ‹check [condition]: Evaluates if something is true. Always goes first.
next [condition]: (Equivalent to elif). Only triggers if the previous check failed.
fail: (Equivalent to else). Triggers if none of the above were true.
вЂ‹Example:
check lives == 0:
show(Game Over)
next lives < 3:
show(Be careful, few lives left)
fail:
show(Still in the fight)
вЂ‹Repetition Blocks (Loops)
Repeats a block of code as long as a condition is true.
loop [condition]: ... endloop
вЂ‹Example:
counter : 1
loop counter <= 5:
show(Round number counter)
counter : counter + 1
endloop
вЂ‹System Commands
version-changes: Displays credit history, version updates, and current development status led by Mr.S and Gemini AI.
вЂ‹Operators:
== (Equal to)
!= (Different from)
вЂ‹/ < (Greater/Less than)
=> (Greater or equal)
вЂ‹/ (Math operations)
вЂ‹Data Engine: Lists (Core)
Group multiple values into a single variable.
Syntax A: <name: item1, item2>
Syntax B: name: (item1, item2)
Display: Use s.name inside a show() to see the full content.
вЂ‹User Extension (ui:)
ui:loading(variable): Draws a dynamic loading bar [в–€в–€в–€в–€......] based on a number (0-100).
ui:color(name): Changes text color (red, green, yellow, blue, magenta, cyan, white, reset).
ui:pos(x, y): Places the cursor at an exact screen coordinate.
вЂ‹Utility Extension (util:)
util:random(min, max) -> variable: Generates a random number and saves it.
util:chance(percentage) -> variable: Returns true or false based on probability.
вЂ‹Audio Extension (sound:)
sound:beep: Triggers a system alert beep.
вЂ‹Data Persistence (File System)
file:save(name): Creates a .txt file (JSON format) with all current memory data.
file:load(name): Restores all variables and lists from a saved file.
вЂ‹Example: file:save(my_progress) saves your data in a format compatible with PC and web browsers.
вЂ‹MR.S ADVICE: Always use clear at the start of your programs for a professional user experience.
